        Creates a transformer that will call f for each incoming ByteString and output its result. After the complete input has been read it will call finish once to determine the final ByteString to post to the output. Empty ByteStrings are discarded.

      • absorbCancellation

        public static <T> akka.stream.scaladsl.Flow<T,T,akka.NotUsed> absorbCancellation()
        INTERNAL API

        Returns a flow that is almost identity but doesn't propagate cancellation from downstream to upstream.

        Note: This might create a resource leak if the upstream never completes. External measures need to be taken to ensure that the upstream will always complete.

        Returns:
        (undocumented)
